        "biography": {
            "errors": [],
            "value": "I am a researcher at the Luxembourg Institute of Socio-Economic Research (LISER), and professor of economics at Pontificia Universidad Catolica del Peru (PUCP). I have also worked and taught in other universities and in other countries. My main motivation for engaging in academic research is to contribute to the understanding, in a robust way, of some of the main challenges in society. In my view, these challenges relate to the fairness of the distribution of economic resources and the tensions that these allocations produce among people. My previous experience as a policy-maker, together with my doctoral training in economics, has shaped my present academic interests and enthusiasm for working in multi-disciplinary environments. My research fields include public economics, economic inequality, redistributive preferences, pensions, and inter-generational transfers. More recently, I have been studying the distribution of wealth in EU countries and designing surveys to capture attitudes toward taxation.",
